snippet.textDisplay:
you actual GP. All types of roller coasters are safe because of many safety procedures and safety locks. If you told ride ops the buckle was undone, the operators would shut down the ride and inspect it. ALSO, the rollercoasters have mid-course brake runs that will stop the cars if there is any problem.

One more thing, YOU DONT HAVE TO BUY A LOCKER TO RIDE ELECTRIC EEL!!! I RODE THAT RIDE (about 6 times with a quick queue pass) AND ITS JUST A SKYROCKET II CLONE.
THERE IS NOTHING SCARY. Literally you are more likely to die while driving to the park than being on a roller coaster. you act like it is such a big deal. 🙄 Stop over exaggerating and making roller coasters seem like torture devices.

And if you don’t support sea world, then don’t go there. Sea world is currently trying to fix their image about animal abuse. They don’t breed anymore and they don’t capture.
